spirit:field.spirit:name: bit32ParityEnable
spirit:field.spirit:description: 0 = 32nd bit is data; 1 = 32nd bit is parity.

spirit:field.spirit:name: decoder
spirit:field.spirit:description: 0: SDI bit comparison disabled 1: SDI bit comparison enabled (and ARINC bits 9 and 10 must match bits 5 and 6, respectively).

spirit:field.spirit:name: matchHeaderBit9
spirit:field.spirit:description: If bit 4 is set, this bit should match ARINC header bit 9 (SDI bit).

spirit:field.spirit:name: matchHeaderBit10
spirit:field.spirit:description: If bit 4 is set, this bit should match ARINC header bit 10 (SDI bit).

spirit:field.spirit:name: reloadLabelMemory
spirit:field.spirit:description: When bit 7 is set to '1', label memory address pointers are initialized to '000'. Set this bit to change the contents of the label memory.

spirit:field.spirit:name: fifoHighWaterMark
spirit:field.spirit:description: 0 = less than programmed level; 1 = FIFO is filled at least up to programmed level.

spirit:field.spirit:name: bit32ParityEnable
spirit:field.spirit:description: 32nd bit is data; 1 = 32nd bit is parity.

spirit:field.spirit:name: fifoHighWaterMark
spirit:field.spirit:description: 0 = less than programmed level; 1 = FIFO is filled at least up to programmed level.

spirit:vendorExtensions.actel-cc:description: Core429_APB provides a complete Transmitter(Tx) and Receiver(Rx). Core429 requires connection to an external CPU. The CPU interface configures the transmit and receive control registers and initializes the label memory. The core interfaces to the ARINC 429 bus through an external ARINC 429 line driver and line receiver. The core include a user testbench for system verification and a comprehensive testbench to verify core performance against the datasheet.
